<TITLE> UK police want car number plate overhaul </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, June 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The registration of car number plates should be completely overhauled to combat a rise in cloning and thefts, British police said on Saturday. The number of plates stolen by thieves, who use them to escape motoring fines or commit crimes, has risen by about 25 percent in the past year to an estimated 40,000. The Association of Police Officers' (Acpo), Vehicle Crime Intelligence Service, told the BBC that it wants all cars to have tamper-proof plates fitted. It also called for a central issuing body for the registration of numbers. Superintendent John Wake told the BBC: "The registration plate is the first form of identification of the vehicle to the general public. "I don't have confidence that beyond that you can identify that that vehicle is the legitimate vehicle for that plate." The rise in the number of speed cameras is one reason why the problem of cloned or stolen plates has mushroomed, because it relies on computer records to determine who owns which car, police said. Paul Smith, founder of the campaign group SafeSpeed.org.uk, rejected the idea that "clever vehicle registration" would solve the issue. "We need to scrap the failed speed camera policy," he said
